<div </div
&nbsp;
"It was a day full of meanings, with gestures that want to affirm the values of the individual rights of the person and of the harmony among peoples - said Minister&nbsp;Sangiuliano&nbsp;-. Eighty years ago the massacre of the Fosse Ardeatine was consumed: 335 people, between military and civilians and many Jewish citizens, were slaughtered by Nazi occupation troops with the fierce collaboration of the fascists. In my memory, I believe that never three ministers, including a German, went along with the shrine of the Ardeatine Fosse. Memory is essential for the rejection of evil to be removed in consciences. Significant and relevant was also the presence at the Portico d'Ottavia where the Roman Jews were razed. I thank the brotherly friends of the Jewish community for having welcomed us at a tragic time in which, after the attack on October 7, reappeared the demon of anti-Semitism. Both in the tragic events re-evoked were positive moments of moral reconstruction. Thanks to the Roth ministra and thanks to the colleague &nbsp;Lollobrigida", he concluded&nbsp;Sangiuliano. &nbsp;
